# Radar-to-Text GenAI for ADAS

This repository contains a **Generative AI project for ADAS systems**, where a pretrained LLM (e.g., LLaMA) is fine-tuned to **generate textual descriptions from radar data**. The goal is to create a first practical GenAI model for radar object classification and scene explanation.
  

---

## ðŸ“Œ Project Overview

- **Input:** Radar data (range-angle-Doppler tensors or radar BEV maps)  
- **Output:** Natural language description of detected objects and scene  
- **Generative AI:** Uses a pretrained **LLaMA** model with **LoRA adapters** for lightweight fine-tuning  
- **Dataset:** Supports synthetic data for initial experiments; can be extended to **CARRADA** or **RadarScenes**  
- **Use Case:** ADAS perception, explainable radar object detection, synthetic scenario generation

---

## âš¡ Features

- Fine-tunes a large language model on radar â†’ text mapping  
- Lightweight LoRA/PEFT adaptation  
- Compatible with GPU and CPU (FP16 recommended)  
- Easy-to-extend for real radar datasets or multimodal fusion (camera + radar)

